NAME
    App::UpdateRinciMetadataDb - Create/update Rinci metadata database

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.03 of App::UpdateRinciMetadataDb (from
    Perl distribution App-UpdateRinciMetadataDb), released on 2014-06-20.

FUNCTIONS
  update_rinci_metadata_db(%args) -> [status, msg, result, meta]
    Create/update Spanel API metadata database.

    This function supports dry-run operation.

    Arguments ('*' denotes required arguments):

    *   dsn* => *str*

        DBI connection DSN.

        Note: has been tested with MySQL and SQLite only.

    *   exclude => *array*

        Perl modules to exclude.

    *   force => *bool*

        Force update database even though module hasn't changed since last
        update.

    *   library => *any*

        Include library path, like Perl's -I.

        Note that some modules are already loaded before this option takes
        effect. To make sure you use the right library, you can use
        "PERL5OPT" or explicitly use "perl" and use its "-I" option.

    *   module* => *array*

        Perl module or prefixes to add/update.

    *   password => *str*

        DBI connection password.

    *   user => *str*

        DBI connection user.

    Special arguments:

    *   -dry_run => *bool*

        Pass -dry_run=>1 to enable simulation mode.

    Return value:

    Returns an enveloped result (an array).

    First element (status) is an integer containing HTTP status code (200
    means OK, 4xx caller error, 5xx function error). Second element (msg) is
    a string containing error message, or 'OK' if status is 200. Third
    element (result) is optional, the actual result. Fourth element (meta)
    is called result metadata and is optional, a hash that contains extra
    information.

